On the eve of this year’s Super Rugby campaign, Stormers coach John Dobson was typically forthright in an interview with a specialist publication about how his charges were going to play in 2020. “We can’t play this Faf de Klerk box-kick stuff. We will empty Newlands.” Dobson is far too sophisticated as a rugby thinker not to elaborate on that statement, but it nonetheless neatly summarised yet again the ideological debate that has defined discourse on South African rugby for years. Up until Rassie Erasmus’ appointment as SA Rugby’s director of rugby in late 2017, the local game was suffering...